<br>
In  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13510.topic">this thread</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> the admin of the Lanys forums handled an attack by the SZ community with a great degree of professionalism and totally kicked their butts by posting not only their IPs but also their ISPs and an e-mail address for each ISP to report the SZer's abuse. Not only have they been banned from Ezboard, had the SZ forums locked down (again), but by reporting these ninnies to their ISPs you can possibly get their internet accounts terminated.<br>
<br>
I'll post an excerpt here from that thread - An SZer wrote to Ezboard complaining their IP was being published on the Lanys board. This is the response they got:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Saw your email at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13510.topic">pub110.ezboard.com/feqasy...510.topic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
I can save you the trouble of a legal complaint - it's denied. We have no<br>
problem with ISPs and IP addresses being posted when they are being used to<br>
stop idiot spammers. Within the next ten minutes every user account that<br>
was involved in the spamming will be globally banned, and then we'll<br>
consider action against the Sullon Zek board - for which you will all get<br>
full credit.<br>
<br>
____________________________<br>
Steven DeMello<br>
President and COO<br>
ezboard, Inc.<br>
sdemello@ezboard.com<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Now my question to you folks is: Would you have any problems if I were to implement the following rule (or something similar)?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If your actions on these forums manage to get you banned, then your IP addresses and ISP info may be published publicly if your crime is considered severe enough.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
